      "raw_text": "SEATTLE, Feb. ct is stated\nthat the railroad commission will\ndo nothing in regard to lowering\nthe east side grain rates at the\npresent time. The Hartman in\nterests have received orders from\ntho commission demanding joint\nrates from eastern Washington\npoints to the Sound. The Harri-\nnanainterests are fighting the or\nder. The commission thinks by the\ntime, the fight is over the Union\nPacific will be here. H. A. Fair\nchild, chairman Of the commission,\nhas left for Walla Walla to meet\nthe o. r. & N. officials and talk\ngrain rates with them."
    }
